{
  "name": "Sniper",
  "type": "feat",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You specialize in targeting foes from far away and attacking while unseen. Whether you're peeking around a corner, perching on a distant rooftop, or aiming from the back line of a squad formation, you favor sniper rifles and prefer to line up the perfect shot rather than rush into combat. You're trained in Stealth. You gain a skill feat for Stealth.</p><p><strong>Exploit:</strong> You ignore the volley trait of guns you wield. You gain one of the following operative feats as a bonus feat: @UUID[Compendium.starfinder-field-test-for-pf2e.feats.Item.XsMsPa52fuYSwj7N]{Keep Them in Your Sights} or @UUID[Compendium.starfinder-field-test-for-pf2e.feats.Item.bichxi9CPayyh0xF]{Scope Sight}.</p><p><strong>Enhanced Exploit:</strong> If you fail your first ranged Strike against your mark using a sniper rifle, that Strike doesn't count toward your multiple attack penalty, and you ignore your sniper rifle's unwieldy trait until the end of your turn.</p>"
    },
